Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stands out as a highly promising energy conversion device, which can convert chemical energy directly into electrical energy.
Titulo: New Oxygen Regulation Strategy to Enhance the Oxygen Reduction Reaction of the Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Cathode through A-Site High-Entropy Engineering

Sentencas: However, the decline in catalytic activity of the cathode becomes a major challenge for the commercialization of SOFC.
Titulo: New Oxygen Regulation Strategy to Enhance the Oxygen Reduction Reaction of the Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Cathode through A-Site High-Entropy Engineering

Sentencas: Here, based on Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (PSCF), two novel A-site high-entropy perovskite cathodes, (Pr0.2Sr0.2La0.2Ba0.2Ca0.2)Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (PSLBCCF) and (Pr0.2Sr0.2La0.2Ba0.2Nd0.2)Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (PSLBNCF), are reported as high-catalyst-activity cathodes for SOFC.
Titulo: New Oxygen Regulation Strategy to Enhance the Oxygen Reduction Reaction of the Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Cathode through A-Site High-Entropy Engineering

Sentencas: The synergistic action of high-entropy elements causes the valence state changes of the A-site Pr element and B-site Co-Fe element, which weakens the bonding energy of the metal element with O.
Titulo: New Oxygen Regulation Strategy to Enhance the Oxygen Reduction Reaction of the Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Cathode through A-Site High-Entropy Engineering

Sentencas: It regulates the adsorption of surface oxygen and the dissociation of lattice oxygen, which enhances the transport of oxygen ions and greatly improves the oxygen reduction reaction and catalytic activity of the cathode.
Titulo: New Oxygen Regulation Strategy to Enhance the Oxygen Reduction Reaction of the Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Cathode through A-Site High-Entropy Engineering

Sentencas: The polarization resistance (R-p) values of PSLBCCF and PSLBNCF cathodes at 750 degrees C are 0.083 and 0.072 Omega cm(2), respectively, which are significantly lower than that of PSCF (0.122 Omega cm(2)).

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the single cell supported by La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta as the electrolyte and high-entropy PSLBNCF as the cathode exhibited a power density of 561.09 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: New Oxygen Regulation Strategy to Enhance the Oxygen Reduction Reaction of the Pr0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ Cathode through A-Site High-Entropy Engineering
